Class Creature

java.lang.Object
Creature
public class Creature extends Object
The Creature class defines what a creature is and its behavior within The Island program.

  • Constructor Details

    • Creature

      public Creature(String species, int hunger, int thirst, int x, int y)
      Main constructor method that contains necessary information about a creature within The Island simulation.
      Parameters:
      species - the type of creature
      symbol - the symbol that will be printed in the console to signify that creature, based on the creature's species. The symbol field is not included in the constructor method, as it is automatically generated based on the creature's species.
      hunger - the creature's hunger level on a scale of 0 (not hungry) to 20 (starving). A creature whose hunger level reaches 20 will die of hunger and be removed from the island.
      thirst - the creature's thirst level on a scale from 0 (not thirsty) to 20 (severe dehydration). A creature whose thirst level reaches 20 will die of thirst and be removed from the island.
      x - the x position of the creature on the island
      y - the y position of the creature on the island

    • Creature

      public Creature()
      This method constructs a randomized creature, using sub-methods to generate a random entry based on established parameters for the species, x, y, hunger, and thirst fields.
